#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:390
msgid ""
"Lost in %1 settings or just looking to discover more features in %1? You can "
"read the [%1 Handbook](%2) to find answers to your questions."
msgstr ""

#. users.help.title
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:393
msgid "Need Help?"
msgstr "助けが必要ですか？"

#. users.help.description
#. %1 app name, %2 link
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:395
msgid ""
"Check %1 on [KDE Forum](%2), maybe someone has already solved a similar "
"problem. And if not, feel free to ask there!"
msgstr ""

#. users.bug.title
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:398
msgid "Found a Bug?"
msgstr "バグを見つけましたか？"

#. users.bug.description
#. %1 app name
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:400
msgid ""
"Bugs in software happen. If you found some in %1, please report them into "
"[our Bugzilla](https://bugs.kde.org). Please do not report bugs on forums or "
"mailing lists — such reports will most likely be overlooked or forgotten by "
"the developers quite soon. To make sure the bug gets noticed by developers "
"and fixed as soon as possible, report it into Bugzilla."
msgstr ""

#. users.feature.title
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:403
msgid "Missing a Feature?"
msgstr "機能が足りていませんか？"

#. users.feature.description
#. %1 app name
#. +> trunk5
#: i18n/en.yaml:405
msgid ""
"%1 has a lot of features, but there’s always a room for one or two more. If "
"you have an idea for an improvement or you are missing a feature in %1, "
"write your suggestion in our [Bugzilla](https://bugs.kde.org) so that the "
"developers can find it and implement it."
msgstr ""

